{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01BAnwuadbU8Gm4GeYZL75Xg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Here is the full implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Complete Implementation\n\n### 1. `api/v1beta1/clusterpodplacementconfig_types.go` — Add `MaxImageInspectionRetries` field\n\nAdd the new field to `ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec`, after `FallbackArchitecture`:\n\n```go\n// In ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec, add after the FallbackArchitecture field:\n\n\t// MaxImageInspectionRetries is the maximum number of times the image inspector will retry\n\t// inspecting an image before giving up.\n\t// +optional\n\t// +kubebuilder:default=5\n\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=20\n\tMaxImageInspectionRetries *int32 `json:\"maxImageInspectionRetries,omitempty\"`\n```\n\nThe full updated struct becomes:\n\n```go\n// ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec defines the desired state of ClusterPodPlacementConfig\ntype ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec struct {\n\t// LogVerbosity is the log level for the pod placement components.\n\t// Valid values are: \"Normal\", \"Debug\", \"Trace\", \"TraceAll\".\n\t// Defaults to \"Normal\".\n\t// +optional\n\t// +kubebuilder:default=Normal\n\tLogVerbosity common.LogVerbosityLevel `json:\"logVerbosity,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// NamespaceSelector selects the namespaces where the pod placement operand can process the nodeAffinity\n\t// of the pods. If left empty, all the namespaces are considered.\n\t// The default sample allows to exclude all the namespaces where the\n\t// label \"multiarch.openshift.io/exclude-pod-placement\" exists.\n\t// +optional\n\tNamespaceSelector *metav1.LabelSelector `json:\"namespaceSelector,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// Plugins defines the configurable plugins for this component.\n\t// This field is optional and will be omitted from the output if not set.\n\t// +optional\n\tPlugins *plugins.Plug